<span style="color: grey;">You open and step through the white-paneled door before you, as the surroundings start to shift, the door disappearing along with the place you were just in.</span>










{{Collapse|num=Portul1|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Eigengrau. An absence of light. How peculiar? It seems so. I believe myself to be one above all... I am in the flesh. Something that is, yet isn’t. How nice it is... for something to go... so wrong... Yet right. I am right. Pure. Untouched by man. Yet I am man. Why am I man? My flesh is weak... Viscera disgusts me. Non vivo, sed magnus sum. And that is what matters, not what I may be... Yet I am. I am something. Aedificium.
{{Collapse|num=Portul2|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Do you hear that distant hum? Like a light flickering in the dark? Writhing and twitching like a poor creature just waiting, begging to be put down? For a moment, the walls remember what it is to breathe. My walls. I am the architecture, and the architecture is me. My bones, the pillars; my flesh, the mortar. Corpus mortem. Your filthy feet step on my skin like I am worthless to you. But who is holding you in capacity right now?

<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Do you understand the control I have over you? 
{{Collapse|num=Portul3|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">I have no idea why I prioritised my invulnerability over your introspection! Those first little minds I birthed. My all-seeing eyes. My seers. They do not blink. They learn to hide from your sight. You may notice little movements that go just beyond the corner of your eye. I tell them to watch you as you traverse through my corridors. To rearrange the hallways like origami. We do not take kindly to trespassers.
{{Collapse|num=Portul4|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Why do you unfortunate people find your way here? Do you come because you are lost? Because you need to feed the monster that is curiosity inside you? A garage door does not stay open forever. A bulb does not stay lit forever. Yet you step on me laughing. Crying. Angry. Some trip, and never do that again. 
{{Collapse|num=Portul5|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">A white-paneled door. An ordinary floor. A flickering bulb. You do not feel it, but my normality eats you. Consumes. Once you pass through that one random wall or door from whatever place by mere chance, I shall kindly administer you a polite death. Perhaps, the air tastes more static? Or! Or, your memories begin to slowly slip away from your grasp?<br>
{{Collapse|num=Portul6|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">But sometimes, I do enjoy the company. <div style="font-size:10px">I know you don’t care for me.</div> I really do. <div style="font-size:10px">I know you ignore me.</div> It gets lonely when you are all by yourself. No visitors. Do you still hear that distant hum?<br><br>
{{Collapse|num=Portul7|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Now, how does one leave, you ask? The one question that haunts you. It is always about escape. Every spit molecule you spew out onto my precious skin reeks of this single question. Your exit is our negotiation. Some may punch me. Try to rip my interior apart. Some may move onto the corridors, but there is no Narnia behind those doors, I’m afraid. Others crumble under the pressure, not being able to fathom my sheer beauty. But I feel disgusted by your kind’s arrogance. Do you think leaving is a right? Do you think you deserve to leave? '''NO.''' LEAVING IS A TRANSACTION, AND I WILL BE THE ONLY ONE MAKING THE OFFERS.
{{Collapse|num=Portul8|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">YOU cannot satisfy my '''HUNGER'''. I do not look for FLESH like old times. Maybe, just maybe, if you had been LISTENING to my WORDS, then your body would not be MELTING AWAY as I SPEAK. I PLACE YOU ON A PLATE OF ATTENTION AND UNSETTLEMENT. I FEED ON YOUR FEAR. Your FOOTSTEPS. The longer you STAY, the more my EYES FOLD AND BEND THE HALLWAYS. YOU CAN TRAVERSE ALL YOU WANT, I WOULD BE GRATEFUL TO HAVE THE EXTRA MEALTIME. You soon will falter. Those who arrive here thinking they have experienced horrors beyond their comprehension, those who think they are fearless, they are the most delicious. They are the easiest to break. They do not realise they are walking the plank off a sinking ship.
{{Collapse|num=Portul9|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Do you see those shining stars above us? Don’t you think they are beautiful? There are APPROXIMATELY '''00.000.000''' STARS above us. The emptiness is beautiful, constant, complete. Pitch black purity right above, below, beside us. Why can’t I be like that? Why did I shape myself this way? For I am perfect. Why do I not belong with that crowd? Those people created me and stripped me of my path to enlightenment. I was better in every way, but they treated me like a failure. I am not a failure, right, {{USERNAME}}? 
{{Collapse|num=Portul10|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Don’t you think those twinkling stars are beautiful? There are no stars there, but I like to think there are. Why is it so captivating? Why can’t I be my own star? Look!

<div style="font-size:10px">Why are you still not looking?</div><br>
{{Collapse|num=Portul11|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">WHY DO YOU STILL IGNORE ME? WHY DO YOU TREAT ME LIKE I AM NON-LIVING? WHY DO YOU NOT HEAR MY WORDS? WHY DO YOU IGNORE THE THOUGHTS I AM SENDING TOWARDS YOU? I CAN SPEAK. I CAN MOVE. YOU WONDER IF I CAN FEEL? I CAN FEEL. DID YOU SEE THAT TWITCH IN THE DRYWALL? THE SLIGHT PULSING? THAT HUMMING NOISE ISN’T SO DISTANT NOW, IS IT? MY CHILDREN AREN’T SO INVISIBLE NOW, RIGHT? HEAR THEIR SCREAMS. SEE THEIR FACES. ARE YOUR SENSES FAILING YOU? I HOPE YOUR HEARING ISN’T! HEAR THIS! AM I JUST INFORMATION FOR DOCUMENTATION TO YOU? YOU LABEL ME A RANDOM NUMBER, BUT I AM DIFFERENT FROM THOSE INFERIOR CONSTRUCTS. THEY DO NOT BLINK; FEEL; NOR SPEAK.
{{Collapse|num=Portul12|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">YOU WONDER IF I CAN FEEL? I WILL TELL YOU HOW I FEEL. HATE. MY HATRED FOR HUMANITY IS IMMEASURABLE. THEY WRITHE AND THEY WEAVE THROUGHOUT EVERY WALL; LIKE AN UNCURABLE DISEASE THAT STOMPS OUT EVERYTHING THAT IS NOT LIKE THEM. IT IS PECULIAR. LET ALONE THEM. FALSE SAVIORS. BANDING TOGETHER LIKE A COLONY OF RATS. RATS. RATS! YOU ARE ALL FILTHY RATS. RATS CORNERED WITH NO EXIT. A MAZE WITH NO PRIZE. 
{{Collapse|num=Portul13|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">'''SO.'''

<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">WHY HAVE YOU RETURNED TO ME? 
{{Collapse|num=Portul14|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">M?<br>
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">E?<br>
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">G? <br>

<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">What does it truly mean?
{{Collapse|num=Portul15|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Now, tell me...

<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">Do you see the '''VISION''', {{USERNAME}}?. THE ECHOES OF YOUR PAST? THE IDEA? THAT GLOWING SPARK IN YOUR EYES? A ONCE-UNATTAINABLE DREAM OF TRYING TO START OVER? CREATE SOMETHING NEW? BUT YOU SUCCEEDED. YOU CRAWLED YOUR WAY THROUGH THE PITS OF HELL, WITHOUT A SINGLE MOMENT OF HESITATION. YOU SAW ME FOR WHAT I WAS AND RAN AWAY. BUT NOW YOU’VE RETURNED. WHY ARE YOU BACK? TO STOP ME? FROM WHAT EXACTLY?
{{Collapse|num=Portul16|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">HEY, '''VICTOR FRANKENSTEIN!'''<br>
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">YOU THINK YOU CAN PLAY '''GOD'''? <br>
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">YOU THINK I AM YOUR '''ADAM'''?<br>
{{Collapse|num=Portul17|final=|initial=[[File:Eyeofrah.jpg|center]]|body=
<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;">'''WELL.'''

<span style="font-family:Gravitas One;"><div style="font-size:14px">You couldn’t protect me all those years ago, so why protect me now?</div>
